column11:
fly fishing;
the sound of the wind
in the reel

Passover darkness -
before the buds burst open;
a child's eyes in death.

from the armoire,
scent of passion in a candle
yet to be burned

Lighting the room,
candle by candle;
a winter evening.

a spider web
caught in my hand;
scent of rain

Deep autumn;
The apple colder
In the tree.

A cold morning;
the pink of tulips
through the mist.

Purple loosestrife;
pale in the
lingering mist.

November fog;
not a tree
to be seen.

Herding sheep;
the prickly smell
of wet wool.

Late summer;
the greyness of dusk
without fireflies.

A spring morning;
The pond's surface blurred
By raindrops.

Afternoon rain;
Scents rise
From the garden.

One just sits;
And blue dawn light floods
his poor house.

Soprano, clear and cool,
and pale violin float;
Above the freeway noise.

This dark night;
Only white spots move
On the calico cat.

Mother's Day;
the smell of roses
near a grave.

Een grijze dag;
het licht verandert niet.
Dan valt de avond.

A pear;
A worm's hole leaves
a bitter taste.

Lumimyrskyssä;
mies pilarin takana
odottaa junaa.

Sumuinen ranta;
jossakin lähellä,
lokkiparvi.

Aamubussissa;
varjo varjon jälkeen
kirjan sivulla.

Kalsea ilta;
kylmän oluen raikkaus
saunan lauteilla.

steam billows
from the cooling tower ::
sunrise

the laughter of children
running uphill . . ;
Gettysburg

vecchio giornale;
in una sala d'aspetto
solo anziani

lilac shadows
scale the garden wall;
slip off into the woods

day-long rain;
I organize
my watercolors

midwinter slush;
the gray breast
of a chipping sparrow

taking a breather;
the rustle 
of poplar leaves

lonely evening;
thunder
rattles the windows

her name on the marble;
birth and death,
the space between

windy day;
the first flurry
of leaves

unknotting 
the hammock ropes;
the scent of burnt leaves

loneliness; 
the trail of a raindrop
down the pane
